 many corpora and existing corpus-analysis software tools are focused on dialogue- and sentence-level analysis, and/or the computational skills needed to efficiently handle large corpora can be daunting to learn.\r\n\r\nPCT is designed with the phonologist in mind and has an easy-to-use graphical user interface that requires no programming knowledge, though it can also be used with a command-line interface, and all of the original code is freely available for those who would like access to the source.", "shortname": "phonologicalcorpustools", "socialnetworks": [{"accounturl": "", "socialnetwork": "Twitter"}, {"accounturl": null, "socialnetwork": "Facebook"}], "status": "active", "summary": "Phonoological CorpusTools provides functions for analyzing corpora", "tools": [{"label": "Activity", "mount_point": "activity", "name": "activity"}, {"label": "Files", "mount_point": "files", "name": "files"}, {"label": "Summary", "mount_point": "summary", "name": "summary", "sourceforge_group_id": 2284958}, {"label": "Reviews", "mount_point": "reviews", "name": "reviews"}, {"label": "Support", "mount_point": "support", "name": "support"}, {"label": "Wiki", "mount_point": "wiki", "name": "wiki"}], "url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/phonologicalcorpustools/", "video_url": null}
